Visualization in R

Lizzie Kumar & Isha Raut
April 2, 2018

ggplot2

  • Library in R that makes nice graphics
  • Makes creation of good looking, useful graphics much easier than base R
  • Can make very diverse plots
  • Works seamlessly with dplyr

Definitions: Aesthetics

  • Mapping of information to a visual property
    • Categorical -> Color
    • Numerical -> Position
    • …

Definitions: Aesthetics

  • Mapping of information to a visual property
    • Categorical -> Color
    • Numerical -> Position
    • Categorical -> Shape
    • Numerical -> Color
    • Numerical -> Size
    • Numerical -> Transparency
    • …

Definitions: "Geoms"

  • A geometric object
    • Point
    • Line
    • …

Definitions: "Geoms"

  • A geometric object
    • Point
    • Line
    • Bar
    • Box-and-whisker
    • Polygon

Basic Plots

  • Scatter Plot
  • Line Chart
  • Bar Chart
  • Histogram
  • Density Plot
  • Box Plot

Initialization

  • Initialize empty graphic
  • We will add our plot to this base plot
  • Feed base plot data, x and y values

Initialization Continued

plot <- ggplot(flights, aes(x = dep_delay, y = arr_delay))
plot

Tip: Specify aesthetics in the main ggplot call to keep the mapping consistent across different geoms

Scatter Plot

plot + geom_point()

Scatter Plot Continued

plot + geom_point(aes(colour=factor(origin)))

We can also add aesthetic mappings for individual geoms using aes()

Scatter Plot Continued

plot + geom_point(colour='blue', size=5, shape=25, alpha=.01)

We can hard-code values within geoms by passing them in as arguments WITHOUT using aes()

Scatter Plot Continued

plot + geom_point(aes(size=distance, shape=factor(origin)), color = 'blue')

Line Chart

plot + geom_point() + geom_smooth()

Line Chart Continued

plot + geom_point() + geom_smooth(span=.01)

Line Chart Continued

plot + geom_point() + geom_smooth(span=.9)

Line Chart Continued

plot + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method='lm')

Line Chart Continued

plot + geom_point() + geom_smooth(aes(colour=factor(origin)), method='lm')

Box Plot

plot2 <- ggplot(flights, aes(distance, air_time))
plot2 + geom_boxplot()

Box Plot Continued

plot2 + geom_boxplot(fill='lightblue', colour='black')

Box Plot Continued

plot2 + geom_boxplot(outlier.colour='red', outlier.shape=25)

Box Plot Continued

plot2 + geom_boxplot(aes(colour=factor(origin)))

Bar Chart

plot <- ggplot(flights, aes(carrier))
plot + geom_bar()

Bar Chart Continued

plot + geom_bar(aes(weight=arr_delay))

Bar Chart Continued

plot + geom_bar(aes(fill=factor(origin)))

Bar Chart Continued

plot + geom_bar(aes(fill=factor(origin)), position='dodge')

Bar Chart Continued

plot + geom_bar(aes(fill=factor(origin)), position='fill')

Histogram

plot <- ggplot(flights, aes(arr_delay))
plot + geom_histogram()

Histogram Continued

plot + geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.5)

Histogram Continued

plot + geom_histogram(bins = 100)

Histogram Continued

plot + geom_histogram(aes(fill=factor(origin)))

Histogram Continued

plot + geom_histogram(aes(colour=factor(origin)))

Density Chart

plot + geom_density()

Density Chart Continued

plot + geom_density(adjust=.01)

Density Chart Continued

plot + geom_density(adjust=100)

Density Chart Continued

plot + geom_density(aes(colour=factor(origin), fill=factor(origin)))

Density Chart Continued

plot + geom_density(aes(colour=factor(origin), fill=factor(origin)), position='stack')

Density Chart Continued

ggplot(flights, aes(arr_delay, ..count.., colour=factor(origin),
                    fill = factor(origin))) +
  geom_density(position='stack')

Other topics

-Interaction : making your ggplots interactive! -Other fun graphs : Maps!

Plotly and ggplot

  • Open source tools that allows interactibe graphics
  • Has a function to neatly convert ggplots to inteactive plots class: small-code
library("plotly")
ggflights<- ggplot2::ggplot(flights, aes(arr_delay, ..count.., colour=factor(origin),fill = factor(origin))) + geom_density(position='stack')

#ggplotly(ggflights)
